<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-12-06T00:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-12-06T00:36:00-05:00" n="973" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d973">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/13980.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Special Agent <persName type="from">Canova</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-12-05T23:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 5, 1914, 11 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The Permanent Commission<note n="71" xml:id="d973fn71">See Mr. Canova’s
                                November 14, 7 p.m.</note> today decided to call a full meeting of
                            the Convention for January 1st. At that meeting thirty accredited Zapata
                            delegates will participate.</p>
                        <p>The Commission criticized President Gutiérrez for some of his
                            appointments. Leading members of the Commission for this reason predict
                            the designation of another provisional president during the first week
                            of January.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Canova</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>